  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The operating envelope is explicitly bounded to flow rates 1–7 L/min and rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM across five operating points; validation experiments cover all boundary points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; each achievedLevel meets or exceeds requiredLevel. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and a documented sensitivity analysis are included. Decision: Accepted — the structured evidence supports adequate credibility for the declared COU.",
